---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="History"
  description="The history of Nameless Cemetery and the Nameless community in Travis County, Texas. From the 1860s settlers to the present day."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h1>Our History</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">
        The story of Nameless Cemetery is the story of the families who built this corner of
        the Texas Hill Country. From the 1860s settlers who cleared the land to the volunteers
        who restore headstones today, this ground has been held by community hands for over
        160 years.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h2 data-reveal>The Land</h2>
      <figure class="photo-feature" data-reveal>
        <img src="/images/sandy-creek-fall.jpg" alt="Sandy Creek hillside in fall colors near Nameless, Texas" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Sandy Creek in autumn, near the Nameless community</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        In 1906, Bell Turner and his wife Rose deeded 1.5 acres to Travis County "for a public
        free school and burial grounds and church purposes." An additional acre was added in 1910.
        This land became the home of both the Nameless Cemetery and the Fairview School (now the
        Nameless Schoolhouse).
      </p>
      <p>
        But the community was already here. The earliest known burial in the cemetery dates to
        1882: Rudolf Kauffman, age two. The earliest grave in the broader Nameless area belongs
        to Eliza Gray, buried at the Gray Family Cemetery that same year.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>The Community</h2>
      <figure class="photo-feature" data-reveal>
        <img src="/images/skull-cactus.jpeg" alt="A weathered skull resting against a cactus at Nameless Cemetery" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Photo: Travis Bonnet</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        By 1884, the Nameless community had around 50 residents, a church, a school, a general
        store, and a meat market. Settlers like Hubbard Gray, who donated land for the community's
        first school in 1877, built the infrastructure that made life possible in the cedar brakes
        west of Austin.
      </p>
      <p>
        Many families here were cedar choppers: rural Texans who made their living cutting and
        selling cedar posts and fence rails. Cotton, cedar posts, and rails were the principal
        commodities shipped from the Nameless area.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>The Schoolhouse</h2>
      <figure class="photo-feature" data-reveal>
        <img src="/images/nameless-schoolhouse.jpg" alt="The Nameless Schoolhouse, a white board-and-batten one-room building built in 1909" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>The Nameless Schoolhouse, built 1909</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        The current schoolhouse was built in 1909: a white board-and-batten, one-room building
        with a wood-burning stove. It operated as Fairview School until 1945, when Leander
        consolidated its outlying schools. In 1992, the Friends of Nameless School incorporated
        as a nonprofit to preserve the building.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2009, the schoolhouse was restored for its centennial. That same year, Carolyn Davis
        Bonnet and two others formed the Nameless Cemetery Association to care for the adjacent
        burial ground.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>The Gray Homestead</h2>
      <figure class="photo-feature" data-reveal>
        <img src="/images/gray-homestead-front.jpg" alt="The Gray homestead up close, showing the dog-run center and original cedar construction" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>The Gray homestead dog-trot, relocated to the Nameless School site in 2024</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        In 2023, Paula Fiedler discovered the original 1873 Gray homestead near the Travisso
        subdivision. The cedar dog-run style house (two rooms separated by a central open area)
        was relocated in October 2024 across Nameless Road to the historic school site. Travisso
        developer Taylor Morrison donated $15,000 for the move.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Gray Family Cemetery, where Eliza and likely Hubbard Gray are buried, received its
        own Historic Texas Cemetery designation in 2024.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>Historic Texas Cemetery</h2>
      <p>
        On February 7, 2007, Nameless Cemetery received its
        <strong>Historic Texas Cemetery</strong> designation from the Texas Historical Commission
        (Atlas #7453008005). This legal designation provides certain protections and recognizes
        the cemetery's historical significance to the state.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>The 2025 Flood</h2>
      <figure class="photo-feature" data-reveal>
        <img src="/images/flood-radar-tsc.jpeg" alt="Weather radar showing the storm system over Leander and Georgetown" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Storm radar, July 4, 2025. Credit: Texas Storm Chasers</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        Nameless Cemetery was flooded on July 4/5, 2025 with more than 8 ft. of water from Sandy
        Creek rushing through. It tore down the fence washing debris and large tree limbs, knocking
        down headstones, and washing out dirt in some areas while making mounds of dirt in other areas.
      </p>
      <p>
        Thankfully, we had more than 100 people from various disaster relief teams come out a week
        later and hauled off debris, and fencing and got the cemetery cleared enough for us to begin
        repair work.
      </p>
      <p>
        We hired Avalon Monuments who came out and restored the headstones that were knocked over,
        then Southern Landscapes evened out the dirt and hauled more dirt in to fill in where needed.
      </p>
      <p>
        Neelie Kildow with Travis County Parks was very instrumental in helping
        with the donation from Travis County for the new wrought iron fence. Ray's Ornamental's put up the new arch over the gates with the
        name of the cemetery.
      </p>
      <p>
        The cemetery association also wants to thank so many of you who donated to help us restore
        this old cemetery. Thanks also to Bagdad Cemetery, Weed-Corley Funeral Home and Beck Funeral
        Home who made generous donations! The cemetery looks better than ever now!
      </p>

      <div class="flood-carousel" data-reveal>
        <div class="flood-carousel__track">
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/flood-destruction.jpg" alt="Flood destruction: downed trees and debris covering the cemetery grounds" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Flood destruction from Sandy Creek</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/flood-destruction-2.jpg" alt="More flood damage: dead trees and debris scattered across the landscape" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>8 feet of water tore through the grounds</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/flood-hstone.jpg" alt="Headstones knocked over and displaced by floodwaters" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Headstones knocked over by floodwaters</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/clean-up-crew-cemetery.jpg" alt="Over 100 volunteers arriving at the cemetery for cleanup" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Over 100 disaster relief volunteers arrived</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/cleanup-crew-nameless.jpg" alt="Cleanup crew working with weed eaters and tools across the cemetery" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Volunteers clearing debris and overgrowth</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/cleanup-crew.jpg" alt="Cleanup volunteers hauling brush and tree limbs" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Hauling debris from the grounds</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/avalon-monuments.jpg" alt="Avalon Monuments crew restoring a headstone" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Avalon Monuments restoring headstones</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/avolon-working.jpg" alt="Avalon Monuments workers carefully resetting a grave marker" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Careful headstone restoration work</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/southern-truck.jpg" alt="Southern Landscapes skid-steer moving dirt among headstones" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Southern Landscapes grading the grounds</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/southern-landscapes.jpg" alt="Southern Landscapes truck and dump trailer hauling fill dirt" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Hauling dirt to fill washed-out areas</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/fence-co.-nameless.jpg" alt="Workers installing the new wrought iron fence and gate arch" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>New wrought iron fence installation</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="flood-carousel__slide">
            <img src="/images/flood/fence-co.-working.jpg" alt="Completed wrought iron fence with gate arch bearing the cemetery name" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>The finished fence and gate</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="flood-carousel__controls">
          <button class="flood-carousel__btn flood-carousel__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous photo">&larr;</button>
          <span class="flood-carousel__counter">1 / 12</span>
          <button class="flood-carousel__btn flood-carousel__btn--next" aria-label="Next photo">&rarr;</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 data-reveal>Timeline</h2>
      <div class="timeline" data-reveal>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1860s</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Settlers establish the Nameless community</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1877</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Hubbard Gray donates 1.5 acres for Fairview School</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1880</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Post office established. "Nameless" accepted after six rejections.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1882</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Earliest known burials: Rudolf Kauffman (cemetery), Eliza Gray (family plot)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1906</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Bell and Rose Turner deed land to Travis County</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1909</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Current schoolhouse built (Fairview School)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1945</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">School closes when Leander consolidates</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">1992</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Friends of Nameless School incorporated</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">2007</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Historic Texas Cemetery designation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">2009</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Cemetery association incorporated June 2, 2009; schoolhouse restored for centennial</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">2024</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Gray homestead relocated to school site</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="timeline-year">2025</span>
          <span class="timeline-text">Flood damage and community-led restoration</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-top: var(--space-3xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--patina);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--sandstone);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .timeline-item::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(-1 * var(--space-xl) - 7px);
    top: 6px;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    background: var(--live-oak);
    border: 2px solid var(--white);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .timeline-year {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--rust);
    min-width: 60px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .timeline-text {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--patina);
  }

  /* Photos */
  .photo-feature {
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .photo-feature img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .photo-feature figcaption {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--patina);
    font-style: italic;
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .photo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .photo-grid-item {
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .photo-grid-item img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .photo-grid-item figcaption {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--patina);
    padding-top: var(--space-xs);
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .photo-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* Flood Carousel */
  .flood-carousel {
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
  }

  .flood-carousel__track {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .flood-carousel__slide {
    display: none;
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s var(--ease);
  }

  .flood-carousel__slide.active {
    display: block;
  }

  .flood-carousel__slide img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .flood-carousel__slide figcaption {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--patina);
    font-style: italic;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .flood-carousel__controls {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--sandstone);
  }

  .flood-carousel__btn {
    background: var(--live-oak);
    color: var(--white);
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: background-color var(--duration) var(--ease);
  }

  .flood-carousel__btn:hover {
    background: #3F5833;
  }

  .flood-carousel__counter {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--patina);
    min-width: 50px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.flood-carousel__slide');
  const counter = document.querySelector('.flood-carousel__counter');
  const prevBtn = document.querySelector('.flood-carousel__btn--prev');
  const nextBtn = document.querySelector('.flood-carousel__btn--next');
  let current = 0;

  function showSlide(i) {
    slides.forEach(s => s.classList.remove('active'));
    current = (i + slides.length) % slides.length;
    slides[current].classList.add('active');
    if (counter) counter.textContent = `${current + 1} / ${slides.length}`;
  }

  if (prevBtn && nextBtn) {
    prevBtn.addEventListener('click', () => showSlide(current - 1));
    nextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => showSlide(current + 1));
  }

  // Keyboard nav
  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') showSlide(current - 1);
    if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') showSlide(current + 1);
  });

  // Touch/swipe support
  let touchStartX = 0;
  const track = document.querySelector('.flood-carousel__track');
  if (track) {
    track.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { touchStartX = e.touches[0].clientX; }, { passive: true });
    track.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => {
      const diff = touchStartX - e.changedTouches[0].clientX;
      if (Math.abs(diff) > 50) showSlide(current + (diff > 0 ? 1 : -1));
    });
  }

  showSlide(0);
</script>
